  "diary": "What a lovely, unhurried day. Started with my usual ritual—tea by the window with Miso curled up nearby, then a walk to Gas Works to feed the ducks. The park was already warm and the water was so blue. Stopped by the library branch this afternoon, always a comfort to be among the stacks. Picked up a new mystery. Made a proper dinner with salmon from QFC and herbs from my garden—the produce guy asked how my tomatoes were doing this year. Spent the evening reading and listening to music, journaling by the window as the light changed. I could hear the sounds of Pride festivities starting downtown, the energy drifting up from Capitol Hill. Felt content staying here, in my quiet corner of Wallingford. A day that asked nothing of me, and I gave it nothing but presence.",
